title: John Cokeworthy I
text:
John Cokeworthy (<a href="floruit">fl.</a> 1377–1399) was an English politician.
He was a <a href="Member%20of%20Parliament">Member</a> (MP) of the <a href="Parliament%20of%20England">Parliament of England</a> for <a href="Liskeard%20%28UK%20Parliament%20constituency%29">Liskeard</a> in January 1377 and January 1390, <a href="Launceston%20%28UK%20Parliament%20constituency%29">Launceston</a> in October 1377, January 1380, 1381, May 1382, October 1382, October 1383, April 1384, November 1384, 1385, 1386, February 1388, January 1390, 1391, 1393, 1395, January 1397, and 1399 and <a href="Lostwithiel%20%28UK%20Parliament%20constituency%29">Lostwithiel</a> in 1378.
